<inglise> The immediate lifting of restrictions on the use of alternative infrastructures could lead to a loss of Esc 24 billion over a period of five years, resulting from a substitution effect (loss of customers to the providers of alternative networks) and a revenue effect (need to reduce tariffs to remain competitive). </inglise>
