<inglise> The comments received </inglise>
<eesti> Laekunud arvamused </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Four undertakings and associations provided comments following the notice published by the Commission on 29 June 1996. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) Komisjoni 29. juunil 1996 avaldatud teatise peale avaldas arvamust neli ettev&otilde;tjat ja &uuml;hingut. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards the lifting of restrictions on operators of mobile and personal communications systems with regard to the establishment of own infrastructure, the majority of comments: </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses mobiil- ja personaalsideoperaatoritele oma infrastruktuuride loomise suhtes kehtestatud piirangute kaotamisega t&otilde;detakse enamikus arvamustes j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - state that there is no justification for granting a derogation in order to allow the Portuguese Government to safeguard itself against the effects of implementing Commission Directive 94/46/EC of 13 October 1994 (5) concerning satellite communications and of the liberalization of non-reserved services including voice services for Closed User Groups ('CUGs') under Directive 90/388/EEC that should have taken effect years ago. </inglise>
<eesti> - erandi tegemine ei ole &otilde;igustatud selleks, et Portugali valitsus saaks ennast kaitsta m&otilde;jude eest, mis kaasnevad komisjoni 13. oktoobri 1994. aasta satelliitsidet k&auml;sitleva direktiivi 94/46/E&Uuml; (5) rakendamisega ja monopoliseerimata teenuste, sealhulgas piiratud kasutajar&uuml;hmadele osutatavate k&otilde;neteenuste liberaliseermisega vastavalt direktiivile 90/388/EM&Uuml;, mis oleks pidanud olema ellu viidud juba aastaid tagasi. </eesti>
<inglise> It is noted that neither satellite communications services nor non-reserved services, including CUG, would replace any sufficient amount of traffic originating or terminating on the GSM networks, as neither are suited for this purpose, </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;helepanu juhitakse sellele, et ei satelliitsideteenused ega monopoliseerimata teenused, sealhulgas teenused kinnistele kasutajar&uuml;hmadele, ei asenda piisavalt andmeliiklust, mis saab alguse v&otilde;i l&otilde;peb GSM-v&otilde;rkudes, sest kumbki nimetatutest ei ole selliseks otstarbeks sobiv; </eesti>
<inglise> - state that it is not reasonable to assume that both GSM operators would cancel all their leased lines in 1997, given that it takes several years to build an alternative network or for new entrants truly to be able to compete with Portugal Telecom. </inglise>
<eesti> - ei ole m&otilde;istlik eeldada, et m&otilde;lemad GSM operaatorid loobuksid k&otilde;igist kasutatavatest p&uuml;siliinidest 1997. aastal, sest alternatiivv&otilde;rgu loomine ja uute turuletulijate arenemine Portugal Telecomi konkurentideks v&otilde;tab aastaid. </eesti>
<inglise> The estimated losses are therefore unnecessarily high. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu on prognoositud kahjud p&otilde;hjendamatult k&otilde;rged. </eesti>
<inglise> A comment refers to a study showing that if Portugal Telecom were to match prices of competing networks (competition effect) rather than keep high prices (substitution effect), the negative financial impact on Portugal Telecom of the Directive would be only equivalent to 1,3 % of revenue instead of 15 % as stated by the Portuguese authorities. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hes arvamuses viidatakse uurimusele, millest ilmneb, et kui Portugal Telecom kohandaks oma hinnad konkureerivate v&otilde;rkude omadega (konkurentsim&otilde;ju) k&otilde;rgete hindade s&auml;ilitamise asemel (asendusm&otilde;ju), oleks majanduslikult negatiivne m&otilde;ju Portugal Telecomile ainult 1,3% tuludest, mitte aga 15% tuludest, nagu v&auml;itsid Portugali ametiasutused. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, comments pointed out that GSM operators bring in new traffic rather than replace Portugal Telecom's traffic in the short term, </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks sellele juhiti arvamustes t&auml;helepanu sellele, et GSM operaatorid loovad pigem uut liiklust, mitte ei asenda l&uuml;hiajaliselt Portugal Telecomi liiklust; </eesti>
<inglise> - claim that the majority of the statistics presented in the Portuguese submission do not take into account all relevant information. </inglise>
<eesti> - suures osas Portugali esitatud statistilistes andmetes ei ole arvesse v&otilde;etud kogu asjaomast teavet. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular it was mentioned that the calculations do not account for the companies within the Portugal Telecom Group who will benefit, rather than suffer, from the Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige mainiti, et arvutustes ei ole arvesse v&otilde;etud Portugal Telecomi kontserni kuuluvaid &auml;ri&uuml;hinguid, kes saavad k&otilde;nealusest direktiivist pigem kasu kui kahju. </eesti>
<inglise> In light of this, the stated impact should be reduced greatly. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud asjaolusid silmas pidades peaks k&otilde;nealune m&otilde;ju olema m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt v&auml;iksem. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards the right of mobile operators to interconnect directly with foreign networks, comments: </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses mobiilsideoperaatorite &otilde;igusega siduda oma v&otilde;rk vahetult v&auml;lisriikide v&otilde;rkudega t&otilde;detakse arvamustes j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - note that the analysis by the Portuguese authorities, which argues that direct interconnection will force Portugal Telecom to lower its tariffs sharply or also lose 15 % of its international fixed traffic to competitors, does not take into account the decrease in costs, as well as the increase in usage, both which would greatly lower the impact on Portugal Telecom, </inglise>
<eesti> - Portugali ametiasutuste anal&uuml;&uuml;sis, milles v&auml;idetakse, et vahetu sidumine sunnib Portugal Telecomi j&auml;rsult oma tariife alandama v&otilde;i kaotama 15% oma tavav&otilde;rgu rahvusvahelisest liiklusest mobiilsideoperaatoritele, ei ole arvesse v&otilde;etud kulude v&auml;henemist ega kasutuse suurenemist, mis v&auml;hendaksid oluliselt m&otilde;ju Portugal Telecomile; </eesti>
<inglise> - state, in reply to the Portuguese authorities' argument that mobile operators will reduce Portugal Telecom's international traffic, that it is highly unlikely that users (most of whom are business users) will use their GSM in place of the PSTN for international calls, </inglise>
<eesti> - vastuseks Portugali ametiasutuste v&auml;itele, nagu v&auml;heneks mobiilsideoperaatorite t&otilde;ttu Portugal Telecomi rahvusvaheline andmeliiklus, peetakse v&auml;ga ebat&otilde;en&auml;oliseks, et kliendid (kellest enamik on &auml;rikliendid) hakkaksid rahvusvahelisteks k&otilde;nedeks kasutama GSM-v&otilde;rke &Uuml;KTV asemel; </eesti>
<inglise> - claim that Portugal Telecom should be able to offer a reduction of at least 30 % on international tariffs. </inglise>
<eesti> - Portugal Telecom peaks suutma langetada rahvusvaheliste k&otilde;nede tariife v&auml;hemalt 30%. </eesti>
<inglise> These discounts are supposedly already given to various large end-users. </inglise>
<eesti> Oletatavasti antakse sellist allahindlust juba mitmele suurele l&otilde;pptarbijale. </eesti>
<inglise> In addition, comments suggest that bulk discounts for mobile operators would create a fairer environment, allowing competing mobile operators companies to offer international tariffs which are more in line with the international fixed voice-telephony tariffs that Portugal Telecom offers. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks sellele mainitakse arvamustes, et mobiilsideoperaatoritele mahult antavad hinnaalandid looksid &otilde;iglasema konkurentsikeskkonna ja v&otilde;imaldaksid konkureerivatel mobiilsideoperaatoritest ettev&otilde;tjatel pakkuda rahvusvaheliste k&otilde;nede tariife, mis oleksid rohkem koosk&otilde;las Portugal Telecomi pakutavate tavav&otilde;rgu k&otilde;neteenuse rahvusvaheliste tariifidega. </eesti>
<inglise> Currently, GSM operators are charged nearly 100 % of Portugal Telecom's retail international call rate (6). One comment shows that this decrease in tariffs would not greatly affect Portugal Telecom's ability to operate, and would bring the benefits that come with lower prices, </inglise>
<eesti> Praegu n&otilde;utakse GSM-operaatoritelt peaaegu 100% Portugal Telecomi rahvusvahelise k&otilde;ne jaehinnast. (6) &Uuml;hest arvamusest ilmneb, et selline tariifide langetamine ei m&otilde;jutaks m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt Portugal Telecomi t&ouml;&ouml;suutlikkust ja samas kaasneks sellega madalamatest hindadest tulenev tulu; </eesti>
<inglise> - generally agree that the actual impact on Universal Service would be in fact, negligible. </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;ldiselt ollakse &uuml;hisel seisukohal, et tegelik m&otilde;ju universaalteenusele oleks &uuml;ldjoontes t&auml;htsusetu. </eesti>
<inglise> It is noted that the only figures included in the documentation offered by the Government were the level of investment needed to fulfil the Universal Service Obligation ('USO'). </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;helepanu juhitakse sellele, et ainsad arvud valitsuse esitatud dokumentides kajastasid universaalteenuse osutamise kohustuse t&auml;itmiseks vajalike investeeringute taset. </eesti>
